[p 
	"Earthbound is a great RPG, designed by Shigesato Itoi in 1994-1995,
	$LF
	"and is also known by the name 
	[em 
		"Mother 2
	]em
	".
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"It is best described as "random", in a good way.
	$LF
	"The game has a great emphasis on a humor, and indeed many things
	$LF
	"in the game are almost caricatured, from subplots to characters.
	$LF
	"It also has a versatile soundtrack.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Although this being a speedrun (tool-assisted at that), most of the
	$LF
	"plot of the game is intact, making this movie very entertaining to
	$LF
	"watch even as a TAS.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Details about each scene and decision in this movie can be read
	$LF
	"in the 
	(__wikiLink|1130S|authors' comments)
	".
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"This movie does not use a death as a shortcut. Although that was a conscious
	$LF
	"decision by the authors, what it actually means was bent to the extreme.
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" The main protagonist, Ness, suffers a mortal blow once. Due to how the game works, he did not die.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" A teddy bear was disintegrated in a battle. Although a party member, it was an inanimate object, and cannot be counted as "death".
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Near the end of the movie, a death-like event is part of the game plot.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
